title: What is the name of the song that has 'oh we oh we oh'? - Quora

response.answer_text: Most famously speaking I think Bobby Brown’s song from the Ghostbusters II soundtrack has this featured, but “oh we oh” has been used in films and songs for decades. I don’t know who first used it. It sounds like a chant you could use to keep everybody focused during a long trek or march. I think the biggest visibilty use was as the chant of the Wicked Witch of the West’s guards in The Wizard of Oz. But after that it’s been used very often!

It might be “The March of the Winkies” from the movie “The Wizard of Oz”:  It also might be “We Know The Way (From "Moana")” from the movie “Moana”:  But I think you are looking for “Scream & Shout” by Britney Spears & will.i.am:
